The paper deals with the problem of rendezvous in an unknown network, which is a fundamental problem in distributed computing. This problem is closely related to the topics of distributed algorithms, graph theory, and network protocols, which are all covered by the arXiv sub-categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also presents solutions to several related problems, such as leader election, perfect renaming, and gossiping, which are all topics in the field of distributed computing and can be classified under the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.AL (Computational Complexity), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.DC and cs.DS, followed by cs.SI, cs.AL, and cs.NI.
